"{\"uid\": \"aljazeera.com-sports-2024-8-10-canadas-b-boy-phil-wizard-wins-first-olympic-breaking-gold-in-paris\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Canadian beat France's Dany Dann in front of a partisan crowd to take the first-ever men's gold medal in breaking.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4, \"end\": 12, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9735911281744847, \"rank\": 0.026263536005140253, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 18, \"end\": 24, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9990494805388951, \"rank\": 0.0009441552795959327, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Save  Share  Canada's B-Boy Phil Wizard won the inaugural Olympic men's breaking gold in Paris and said he hoped it \\\"opens doors to people\\\" involved in the high-energy dance sport.\", \"from\": 120, \"to\": 300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 133, \"end\": 139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9745771332350563, \"rank\": 0.01562657356437826, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 209, \"end\": 214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996668976, \"rank\": 3.3309043565769504e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phil Wizard, whose real name is Philip Kim, beat France's B-Boy Dany Dann in Saturday's final amid the opulent grandeur of the Place de la Concorde, with B-Boy Victor of USA taking bronze.\", \"from\": 302, \"to\": 490, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 334, \"end\": 344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\", \"score\": 0.9999999991202912, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philip Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\"}, {\"begin\": 351, \"end\": 357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9990494805388951, \"rank\": 0.0009441552795959327, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 429, \"end\": 449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 0.999999991220875, \"rank\": 8.779072703847505e-09, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking, better known as breakdancing, is making its first and possibly last appearance at the Olympics, having been left off the programme for Los Angeles 2028.\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 637, \"end\": 653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles 2028\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phil Wizard said that breaking was \\\"an underappreciated sport\\\" and hoped its Olympic debut would change people's minds.\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 775, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope that today was a perfect example of showing the world how incredible breaking is - that was truly my only goal here,\\\" said the 27-year-old, a former world champion.\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 949, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am so grateful and so happy to come out with the win but more than anything, I just wanted to show the world what breaking is.\\\"\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition saw 16 dancers, known as B-Boys, going head-to-head in a series of battles, starting with a pool stage before moving to a knock-out round.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1237, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Phil Wizard had the crowd against him in the final against local hero Dany Dann, a 36-year-old with blue hair whose real name is Danis Civil.\", \"from\": 1239, \"to\": 1380, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Canadian soon had them eating out of his hand thanks to his incredible routine, for which the judges awarded him a 3-0 victory.\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1517, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1390, \"end\": 1398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9735911281744847, \"rank\": 0.026263536005140253, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was stressed out of my mind,\\\" said Phil Wizard.\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's been a whirlwind of emotion.\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I cried my eyes out because I was so scared to do this.\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1661, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is been a lot of pressure, a lot of expectations - I am glad I was able to deliver.\\\"\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Danny Dann, a former European champion, said he felt like he had \\\"represented breaking\\\" to the world.\", \"from\": 1756, \"to\": 1857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1777, \"end\": 1794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Figure_Skating_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9976496257168224, \"rank\": 0.0021658047597492556, \"text\": \"European champion\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Figure_Skating_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Figure_Skating_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am delighted, I really did not think I would win this medal,\\\" he said, revealing that he dyed his hair blue because it was his \\\"lucky colour\\\".\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 2004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just went there to see how things would go and I am going home with a silver medal!\\\"\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2093, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the spectacular moves on show, Phil Wizard said the panel of judges were looking for \\\"something new every round\\\".\", \"from\": 2095, \"to\": 2216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You may well think it's the most explosive, crazy dynamic movements that score the most points,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2324, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But in breaking, there is a lot of different categories and the most important thing is originality and diversity of movement.\\\"\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2454, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The B-Boys perform on a circular stage, accompanied by DJs pumping out hip-hop classics and MCs hyping up the crowd.\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking originated in the block parties held in the Bronx in New York in the 1970s.\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2627, \"end\": 2632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"score\": 0.9999990806947741, \"rank\": 9.192959532240726e-07, \"text\": \"Bronx\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\"}, {\"begin\": 2636, \"end\": 2644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999997723660076, \"rank\": 2.2347906543078916e-07, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"B-Boy Victor, also known as Victor Montalvo, said the competition represented \\\"the true essence of hip hop and breaking culture\\\".\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2789, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2660, \"end\": 2665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.820635685597716e-33, \"text\": \"B-Boy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\"}, {\"begin\": 2666, \"end\": 2672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.9999127600440991, \"rank\": 7.793255921691412e-05, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 2688, \"end\": 2694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.9999127600440991, \"rank\": 7.793255921691412e-05, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 2695, \"end\": 2703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalvo_Beach\", \"score\": 0.9894755037246608, \"rank\": 0.0064197935718665715, \"text\": \"Montalvo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalvo_Beach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalvo_Beach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We just want to make sure that we show everyone that it's a dance, first of all,\\\" said Victor, who beat Japan's Shigekix for the bronze medal.\", \"from\": 2791, \"to\": 2934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2879, \"end\": 2885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.9999127600440991, \"rank\": 7.793255921691412e-05, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 2896, \"end\": 2901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9829523631953683, \"rank\": 0.010324700645482899, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's all about self-expression, it's all about originality.\", \"from\": 2936, \"to\": 2996, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not just about big moves.\\\"\", \"from\": 2997, \"to\": 3028, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Al Jazeera English:\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3074, \"entities\": []}]}"